# 📊 Day 1 – Product Metrics & Business Thinking

## 🎯 Objective
Understand key product metrics and apply them to real-world business scenarios.

---

## 🟡 Case Study 1: Swiggy

### 🔹 Retention
Percentage of users who continue to place orders over time.

### 🔹 Churn
Users who stop ordering from the platform.

---

## 🟡 Case Study 2: Amazon

### 🔹 Conversion
Percentage of users who complete a purchase out of total visitors.

### 🔹 DAU / MAU
Number of users actively engaging with the platform daily/monthly (browsing, searching, purchasing).

---

## 🧠 Business Case 1: Increase in Churn (Swiggy)

### Possible Reasons:
- Poor food quality  
- Delayed deliveries  
- Increase in pricing  

---

## 🧠 Business Case 2: Drop in Conversion (Amazon)

### Possible Reasons:
- High product pricing  
- Poor product descriptions or reviews  
- Complex checkout process  

---

## 🚀 Key Learnings
- Metrics should be linked to business outcomes  
- Conversion is a pre-purchase metric  
- Churn is a post-experience metric  
- Always analyze data with a business perspective  

